{
  "stem": "14463.1",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my brother was the big boy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And, and my grandparents-- and my grandparents, both of them, Simcha and Malka, and my uncles, and my aunties, and my cousins.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I have got such wonderful memories on those time from, from the time I was born, till the war started.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And what else can I tell you about Chrzanow?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, the holidays-- Rosh Hashanah, Yom Kippur, Shavis, Pesach.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Pesach when it came, Pesach, I remember very well.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Of course, Pesach was the beginning of spring, so everybody got dressed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Everybody got new clothes, from top to bottom.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And of course, we went to the-- and grandfather had the seder, and the whole family.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a huge family, and also friends.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember just the shavirim, which I was in my grandfather's place, extremely well, extremely well.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then Rosh Hashanah was so solemn.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Yom Kippur was so solemn.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was just unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Yom Tovim in Chrzanow was something incredible.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And you know, also Shabbos afternoon, the whole city had a bit of a [NON-ENGLISH] for one hour, an hour and a half.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they all walked now [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Is they used to walk-- go for walk after Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, it was their relaxation, whole families together was walking.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Reb Simcha, Reb Moishe, Reb This, Reb That.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they greeted each other in the streets.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there was the main thoroughfare in Chrzanow, where there was the better part of Chrzanow, where the nicer homes were.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My grandfather had a villa there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it's beside the point.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And all the people used to walk in there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so I remember that Shabbatanz and the Yom Tovim.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was so deep in my psyche, inside me, that it's never left me.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
